abstract: CHICAGO, Nov. 4 -- Wheat was weak to-day, with a good trade. Longs were the principal sellers, although Pardridge and shorts lent a hand to the downward course. The selling was mainly of the December option, with considerable of it changed to the May. As delivery day for December approaches holders are concluding either to protect their losses or transfer their contracts to later months rather than run any farther risk.

It would in no way strengthen the peace of Europe, which the triple alliance did not intend to affect, but rather would compromise it, and would compel Great Britain to lake extra precautions in the Mediterranean.
